obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-2
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Page 2`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE HINDI SAHITYA SAMMELAN ACT, 1962`
  line `A CT N O. 13 OF 1962`
  line `[30 th March, 1962. ]`
  line `An Act to declare the institution known as the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan having its head office at`
  line `Allahabad to be an institution of national importance and to provide for its incorporation and`
  line `matters connected therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Thirteenth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called The Hindi Sahitya Sammelan`
  line `Act, 1962.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `2. Declaration of the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan as an institution of national`
  line `importance. — Whereas the objects of the institution known as the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan which has its`
  line `head office at Allahabad are such as to make the institution one of national importance, it is hereby`
  line `declared that the institution known as the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan, is an institution of national importance.`
  line `3. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ appointed day ” means the date on which this Act comes into force;`
  line `( b ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( c ) “ Sammelan ” means the institution known as the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan, incorporated under`
  line `this Act;`
  line `( d ) “ Society ” means the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan which has its head office at Allahabad and is`
  line `registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1960).`
  line `4. Incorporation. — ( 1 ) The first members of the Sammelan and all persons who may hereafter`
  line `become members thereof in accordance with the rules made in this behalf, so long as they continue to hold`
  line `membership thereof, are hereby constituted a body corporate by the name of the Hindi Sahitya Sammelan.`
  line `( 2 ) The Sammelan shall have perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract and may by that name sue`
  line `and be sued`
  line `( 3 ) The head office of the Sammelan shall be at Allahabad.`
  line `2 [( 4 ) The first members of the Sammelan shall be —`
  line `(a) all persons who, immediately before the appointed day, were members of the Society;`
  line `(b) all persons who, before that day, have been Presidents of the Society; and`
  line `(c) all persons who, before that day, were awarded the Mangla Parshad Paritoshik by`
  line `the Society.]`
  line `5. Effect of incorporation of Sammelan. — On and from the appointed day,`
  line `( a ) any reference to the Society in any law (other than this Act) or in any contract or other`
  line `instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the Sammelan;`
  line `3 [( b ) all property, movable or immovable, of the Society shall be the property of the Sammelan;]`
  line `1. 28th June, 1962 vide notification No. S.O. 1954(E), dated 25th June, 1962, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `Sec. 3( ii ).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1963, s. 2, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 28-6-1962).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 25-1-1963).`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `( c ) all rights and liabilities of the Society shall 1 *** be the rights and liabilities of the`
  line `Sammelan; and`
  line `( d ) every person employed for the Society immediately before the appointed day shall hold his`
  line `office or service in the Sammelan by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the same`
  line `terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension, leave, gratuity, provident`
  line `fund and other matters as he would have held the same if this Act had not been passed, and shall`
  line `continue to do so unless and until his appointment is terminated or until his tenure or terms and`
  line `conditions are duly altered by the rules made in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to any such employee, his employment may be`
  line `terminated by the Sammelan in accordance with the terms of the contract with the employee or, if no`
  line `provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by the Sammelan of compensation equivalent`
  line `to three month’s remuneration in the case of permanent employees and one month’ s remuneration in the`
  line `case of permanent employees.`
  line `6. Functions of Sammelan. — Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made t hereunder, the`
  line `Sammelan shall perform the following functions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) to promote the spread of Hindi language and to develop it and secure its enrichment in the`
  line `manner indicated in Article 351 of the Constitution;`
  line `( b ) to work for the promotion, development and advancement of Hindi literature in India and`
  line `foreign countries and to print and publish such literature;`
  line `( c ) to work for the promotion, development and advancement of Devanagari script, and to print`
  line `and publish literature of other Indian languages in Devanagari script;`
  line `( d ) to arrange for the holding of examinations through the medium of Hindi language and to confer`
  line `degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions;`
  line `( e ) to establish and maintain schools, colleges and other institutions for instruction in Hindi`
  line `language and Hindi literature and also to affiliate schools, colleges and other institutions for its`
  line examinations;
  line `( f ) to affiliate institutions having for their object the promotion of Hindi language and`
  line `Hindi literature;`
  line `( g ) to award honorary degrees and other academic distinctions to persons who may have rendered`
  line `distinguished service to the cause of Hindi;`
  line `( h ) to institute and award prizes (Partioshiks) to distinguished scholars in Hindi;`
  line `( i ) to promote and encourage research in Hindi language and Hindi literature;`
  line `( j ) to co-operate with other institutions having objects similar to those of the Sammelan, in such`
  line `manner as may be conducive to their common objects;`
  line `( k ) to receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Government and to receive`
  line `bequests, donations or transfers of moveable and immoveable properties from testators, donors or`
  line `transferors, as the case may be;`
  line `( l ) to deal with any property belonging to or vested in the Sammelan in such manner as the`
  line `Sammelan may deem fit for advancing the objects of the Sammelan:`
  line `( m ) with the approval of the Central Government, to borrow on the security of the property of the`
  line `Sammelan money for the purposes of the Sammelan,`
  line `( n ) to perform such other functions as may be deemed necessary by the Sammelan for advancing`
  line `the cause of Hindi language and Hindi literature or as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the`
  line `performance of all or any of the above functions.`
  line `1. The words “be transferred to, and” omitted by Act 1 of 1963, s. 3 ( w.e.f. 25-1-1963).`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `7. Governing Body. — ( 1 ) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the`
  line `Sammelan shall vest in a Governing Body, by whatever name called.`
  line `( 2 )The Governing Body shall consist of such number of persons not exceeding fifty-five as the Central`
  line `Government may from time to time determine, of whom not more than seven shall be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government from among educationists of repute or eminent Hindi scholars, and the remaining`
  line `members shall be chosen in accordance with the rules made in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the powers and functions of the Governing Body, the term of`
  line `office of, and the allowances, if any, payable to members thereof, the procedure to be followed by the`
  line `Governing Body for the transaction of its business, the quorum necessary therefore and the manner of`
  line `filling casual vacancies among the members thereof shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line `8. First Governing Body and its duties. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazeette constitute the first Governing Body`
  line `consisting of a Chairman, a Secretary, and thirteen other mem bers to be appointed by that Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The thirteen members referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be chosen as follows: —`
  line `( i ) one member to represent the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with education;`
  line `( ii ) one member to represent the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with finance;`
  line `( iii ) not more than three members from among the former Presidents of the Society; and`
  line `( iv ) the remaining number from among persons who are. in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, eminent in the field of Hindi language or Hindi literature.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be the duty of the first Governing Body of the Sammelan, —`
  line `( a ) to perform all functions of the Sammelan and to carry on the administration of the affairs of the`
  line `Sammelan until a Governing Body is constituted in accordance with the provisions of section 7;`
  line `( b ) to make the rules with the approval of the Central Government;`
  line `( c ) to determine the first members of the Sammelan within the meaning of sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 4;`
  line `( d ) to take all necessary steps for the constitution of the Governing Body in accordance with`
  line `such rules;`
  line `( e ) to perform such other functions as it may consider necessary.`
  line `9. Term of office and procedure of first Governing Body and allowan ces payable to members`
  line `thereof. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of section 14, the members of the first Governing Body shall hold`
  line `office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) All questions at a meeting of the first Governing Body shall be decided by a majority of the`
  line `members present thereof, and in the case of an equality of votes the Chairman or, in his absence, any other`
  line `person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line `( 3 ) The quorum to constitute a meeting of the first Governing Body shall be 1 [five] members.`
  line `( 4 ) The members shall be paid out of the Fund of the Sammelan such 2 [salary or allowances or both]`
  line `may be prescribed and until so prescribed, as may be specified by the Central Government in this be halt.`
  line `10. First Governing Body to take over management of properties of`
  line `Sammelan. — Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force or in any order of a court, the first Governing Body shall take over the management, control and`
  line `administration of all the properties vested in the Sammelan.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1963, s. 4, for “three” (w.e.f. 25-1-1963).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “allowances” (w.e.f. 25-1-1963).`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `11. Determination of first members. — ( 1 ) The first Governing Body shall, as soon as may be, cause`
  line `to be prepared, subject to such instructions, it any, as it may receive from the Central Government, a list of`
  line `all persons who are to be considered as first members of the Sammelan within the meani ng of sub - section`
  line `( 4 ) of section 4.`
  line `( 2 ) The list shall be published in such manner as may be directed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 3 ) If at any time after the publication in the list of first members under sub-section ( 2 ), it appears to`
  line `the first Governing Body that the name of any person has been wrongly omitted from, or wrongly entered`
  line `in the list, it may order such name to be inserted or omitted from that list and the list shall be amended`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided that no order omitting the name of any person from the list shall be made unless that person`
  line `has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such omission.`
  line `( 4 ) No persons other than the persons named in the list prepared under this section shall be considered`
  line `as first members of the Sammelan within the meaning of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 4.`
  line `12. Rules to be made by the first Governing Body. — ( 1 ) The first Governing Body shall, as soon as`
  line `may be, make rules in respect o f the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the matters relating to membership, including the qualifications and disqualifications for`
  line `membership of the Sammelan;`
  line `( b ) the powers and functions of the Governing Body; the term of office of, and the allowances, if`
  line `any, payable to, members thereof; the procedure to be followed by the Governing Body for the`
  line `transaction of its business, the quorum necessary therefore and the manner of filling casual vacancies`
  line `among the members thereof;`
  line `( c ) the conduct of elections for the constitution of the Governing Body and the decisions on doubts`
  line `and disputes at or in connection with the said elections;`
  line `( d ) the appointment of an executive committee or any other committee for carrying on the`
  line `functions of the Governing Body or of the Sammelan; the constitution, powers and duties of such`
  line `committees and the allowances, if any, payable to the members thereof;`
  line `( e ) the procedure and the forms for the maintenance of books of accounts and other registers and`
  line `statements for the purposes of this Act;`
  line `( f ) the appointment, control and other conditions of service of the employees of the Sammelan;`
  line `( g ) the conduct of correspondence, execution of documents and contracts for or on behalf of the`
  line Sammelan;
  line `( h ) the conduct and prosecution of suits and proceedings by or against the Sammelan;`
  line `( i ) the matters relating to the affiliation of schools, colleges, and other institutions with the`
  line Sammelan;
  line `( j ) the matters relating to the award of degrees and academic distinctions by the Sammelan:`
  line `( k ) the matters relating to the award of prizes (Paritoshiks) by the Sammelan;`
  line `( l ) the procedure for the amendment of the rules;`
  line `( m ) such other matters as may be necessary for the performance of the functions of the Sammelan.`
  line `( 2 ) A draft of the rules proposed to be made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be forwarded to the Central`
  line `Government for approval and that Government may approve the same with or without modifications.`
  line `( 3 ) No rules made under this section shall have effect until they are approved by the Central`
  line `Government and are published by the first Governing Body in such manner as the Central Government`
  line `may, by order direct.`
  line `( 4 ) A copy of the rules so made shall be laid, as soon as may be after they are made before each House`
  line `of Parliament`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `13. Ele ctions to Governing Body. — The first Governing Body shall, within six months of its`
  line `constitution or within such further period as may be specified by the Central Government, arrange to hold`
  line `elections to the Governing Body in accordance with the provisions o f the rules made under section 12 and`
  line `take such further steps as may be necessary for its due constitution within the period specified as aforesaid.`
  line `1 4. Dissolution of first Governing Body. — On the constitution of the Governing Body under`
  line `section 7 in accordance with the rules made under section 12, the first Governing Body shall cease to exist`
  line `and stand dissolved.`
  line `15. Fund of the Sammelan. — ( 1 ) The Sammelan shall maintain a F und to which shall be credited —`
  line `( a ) all fees and other charges received by the Sammelan;`
  line `( b ) all moneys received by the Sammelan by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions,`
  line `bequests or transfers; and`
  line `( c ) all moneys received by the Sammelan in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line `( 2 ) The Fund shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Sammelan in the performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act, including allowances, if any, payable to the members of the Governing Body or`
  line `of any Committee and the salaries and allowances, if any, of the employees of the Sammelan.`
  line `16. Accounts and audit. — ( 1 ) The Sammelan shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance - sheet in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the Sammelan shall, once at least in every year, be audited by a chartered`
  line `accountant in practice within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949, to be appointed`
  line `annually by the Sammelan;`
  line `Provided that no member of the Sammelan who is a chartered accountant or a person who is in`
  line `partnership with such member shall be eligible for appointment as an auditor under this section.`
  line `( 3 ) Every auditor shall, in the performance of his duties, have at all reasonable times access to the`
  line `books, accounts and other documents of the Sammelan.`
  line `( 4 ) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each year, the audited accounts of the Sammelan`
  line `together with the audit report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line `17. Power to make rule. — ( 1 ) The Governing Body may, from time to time, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the purposes of this Act and such rules may amend or repeal the rules made under sectio n 12.`
  line `( 2 ) No rules made under this section shall have effect until they are approved by the Central`
  line `Government and are published by the Governing Body in the prescribed manner.`
  line `18. Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc. — No act of the Sammelan, or of`
  line `the Governing Body, or of any other body set up under the rules made in this behalf shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of —`
  line `( a ) any vacancy therein, or defect in the constitution thereof, or`
  line `( b ) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member`
  line `thereof, or`
  line `( c ) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
  line `19. Power to remove difficulties. — If any difficulty arises in giving effect to th e provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provision or give`
  line `such directions not inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or expedient`
  line `for removing the dif ficulty.`
